## 2. Awesome Copilot Instructions — Exactly What to Copy

The `.github/instructions/` folder **does not yet exist** in your project. This is the **single biggest thing you need to do before starting coding**. Copilot cannot auto-enforce any rules without these files.

Copy **exactly these 8 files** from `awesome-copilot/instructions/` to `Event-Ticketing-Platform/.github/instructions/`:

| File to Copy | `applyTo` pattern | What it enforces |
|---|---|---|
| `springboot.instructions.md` | `**/*.java, **/*.kt` | Constructor injection, `@Transactional`, `@RequiredArgsConstructor`, `Instant`, no `@Autowired` |
| `security-and-owasp.instructions.md` | `**/*.java` | OWASP rules, JWT handling, XSS prevention, input validation |
| `performance-optimization.instructions.md` | `**/*.java` | Redis patterns, N+1 prevention, `readOnly=true`, connection pooling |
| `oop-design-patterns.instructions.md` | `**/*.java` | Design patterns enforcement (State, Strategy, Factory, etc.) |
| `object-calisthenics.instructions.md` | `**/*.java` | Clean code rules, no magic numbers, single responsibility |
| `spec-driven-workflow-v1.instructions.md` | `**` | Spec lifecycle enforcement across all files |
| `self-explanatory-code-commenting.instructions.md` | `**/*.java` | Code comment quality rules |
| `update-docs-on-code-change.instructions.md` | `**/*.java, **/*.md` | Forces doc updates when code changes |

Also create `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — the master config that is ALWAYS active regardless of file type.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Without these 8 files in `.github/instructions/`, Copilot is running **without guardrails**. All fixes in `Phase1A_Adjustments_and_Fixes.md` depend on these instructions being active to be auto-enforced. This is the #1 action item before Day 1 coding.

