## 4. Phase1A_Adjustments_and_Fixes.md — Complete Fix Inventory

All 21 entries, each assessed:

| Fix ID | Day | Severity | Summary | Assessment |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **1.1** | Day 1 | 🔴 CRITICAL | `Instant` instead of `LocalDateTime` + Flyway `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Well-specified with exact code. Top gap in analysis. |
| **1.2** | Day 1 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | PostgreSQL ENUM for `user_role` | Correct — prevents silent bad data at DB level |
| **1.3** | Day 1 | 🟢 GOOD | Soft delete `deleted_at` on bookings table | Correctly positioned; needs `@Where` clause |
| **2.1** | Day 2 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` on all read methods | Class-level default pattern is the right approach |
| **2.2** | Day 2 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | Constructor injection via `@RequiredArgsConstructor`, ban `@Autowired` | Enforce from Day 2, not retrofitted on Day 20 |
| **5.1** | Day 5 | 🔴 CRITICAL | Lua floor guard in `reserveSeat()` — prevents negative inventory | Exact Lua script provided; the `-2` (key missing) case correctly handled |
| **5.2** | Day 5 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | Redis startup health block until warm-up completes | `InventoryWarmupHealthIndicator` is correct pattern |
| **8.1** | Day 8 | 🔴 CRITICAL | TOCTOU double-check availability INSIDE the distributed lock | The core race condition fix — user-scoped lock + inside-lock re-check |
| **8.2** | Day 8 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `CHECK_IN` guard — organizer-only + event-scoped | Both `@PreAuthorize` (HTTP) AND guard (SM layer) required |
| **8.3** | Day 8 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | Distributed lock on `@Scheduled` expiry job | 25s lock TTL < 30s interval is the correct design |
| **9.1** | Day 9 | 🔴 CRITICAL | Return 200 AFTER DB commit; controller must NOT be `@Transactional` | Correctly motivated — return 500 on DB failure to trigger Stripe retry |
| **9.2** | Day 9 | 🔴 CRITICAL | Webhook idempotency via `DataIntegrityViolationException` catch | DB UNIQUE constraint is the hard guard, not `existsBy` check |
| **10.1** | Day 10 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `DENY_REFUND` notification action for silent refund denials | Gap in original plan — users get no notification without this |
| **10.2** | Day 10 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | QR generation offloaded to async `ticket.generation.queue` | Sync ZXing for 50-ticket bookings in webhook is unacceptable |
| **11.1** | Day 11 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `CANCELLED` state + `EVENT_CANCELLED` event from 3 source states | Fundamental gap — CONFIRMED, RESERVED, PAYMENT_PENDING all need this |
| **11.2** | Day 11 | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `RELEASE` event caller must be documented or removed | Orphan transitions are dangerous; recommended to remove `AVAILABLE` from `BookingState` |
| **12.1** | Day 12 | 🟢 GOOD | `refund_denial_reason` field for user transparency | Simple but high UX value |
| **16.1** | Day 16 | 🔴 CRITICAL | Test Lua floor guard with 100-thread concurrency test (Testcontainers Redis) | Without this, a Lua syntax error goes undetected |
| **CC-1** | All days | 🟢 GOOD | `X-Correlation-ID` propagation via `CorrelationIdFilter` + MDC + RabbitMQ headers | Full implementation provided including listener restore pattern |
| **CC-2** | All days | 🟡 IMPORTANT | `BusinessConstants.java` — no magic numbers anywhere | All constants listed; create on Day 1 |
| **PW3-1** | Pre-Day 9 | 🔴 CRITICAL | Create Stripe + Railway accounts on Day 1, not Day 9 | Gap not in original plan — costs 60 min on your tightest day |

> [!CAUTION]
> You have **6 CRITICAL fixes** (1.1, 5.1, 8.1, 9.1, 9.2, 16.1, PW3-1). Every one has a DB-level or Redis-level consequence: oversell, webhook loss, wrong expiry, race condition, untested Lua script. None can be deferred.

